// A `defer` opened INSIDE a loop body must fire when `break` exits the loop
// (Risk 3, LESSONS `cleanup-all-exits`). The break handler flushes the
// in-loop defer window (`active_scopes[loop_scope_depth..]`) before jumping
// to `exit_bb`, so deferred cleanup that was registered inside the loop body
// still runs on the break path.
//
// The deferred `exit(9)` is registered inside the loop body, then `break`
// leaves the loop. If the in-loop defer fires on break (correct), the process
// exits 9 and never reaches `return 0`. If the break path failed to flush the
// in-loop defer window, control would fall through to `return 0` and exit 0.
// Observing exit code 9 proves the in-loop defer ran on the break path.
fn main() -> i64 {
    loop {
        defer exit(9);
        break;
    }
    return 0;
}
